swVlanCtrlMode.name: swVlanCtrlMode
swVlanCtrlMode.description: This object controls which Vlan function will be enable (or disable) when the switch hub restart at the startup (power on) or warm start.

swVlanInfoStatus.name: swVlanInfoStatus
swVlanInfoStatus.description: This object indicates which Vlan function be enable (or disable) in mandatoryly stage. There are no effect when change swVlanCtrlMode vlaue in the system running.

swVlanSnmpPortVlan.name: swVlanSnmpPortVlan
swVlanSnmpPortVlan.description: Indicates the Vlan which the SNMP port belongs to. The value range is 1 to 4094.

swMacBaseVlanMaxNum.name: swMacBaseVlanMaxNum
swMacBaseVlanMaxNum.description: The maximum number of Mac base Vlan allowed by the system.

swMacBaseVlanAddrMaxNum.name: swMacBaseVlanAddrMaxNum
swMacBaseVlanAddrMaxNum.description: The maximum number of entries in Mac-based Vlan address table.

swMacBaseVlanCtrlTable.name: swMacBaseVlanCtrlTable
swMacBaseVlanCtrlTable.description: A table that contains information about MAC base Vlan entries for which the switch has forwarding and/or filtering information. This information is used by the transparent switching function in determining how to propagate a received frame.

swMacBaseVlanCtrlEntry.name: swMacBaseVlanCtrlEntry
swMacBaseVlanCtrlEntry.description: A list of information about a specific MAC base Vlan configuration portlist for which the switch has some forwarding and/or filtering information.

swMacBaseVlanDesc.name: swMacBaseVlanDesc
swMacBaseVlanDesc.description: A textual description of the Mac Base Vlan for memorization. The string cannot set to empty string. There is a default value for this string.

swMacBaseVlanMacMember.name: swMacBaseVlanMacMember
swMacBaseVlanMacMember.description: This object indicates the total number of MAC addresses contained in the VLAN entry.

swMacBaseVlanCtrlState.name: swMacBaseVlanCtrlState
swMacBaseVlanCtrlState.description: This object indicates the MacBase Vlan state.

swMacBaseVlanAddrTable.name: swMacBaseVlanAddrTable
swMacBaseVlanAddrTable.description: A table that contains information about unicast or multicast entries for which the switch has forwarding and/or filtering information. This information is used by the transparent switching function in determining how to propagate a received frame. Note that the priority of MacBaseVlanAddr table entries is lowest than Filtering Table and FDB Table, i.e. if there is a table hash collision between the entries of MacBaseVlanAddr Table and Filtering Table inside the switch H/W address table, then Filtering Table entry overwrite the colliding entry of MacBaseVlanAddr Table. This state is same of FDB table. See swFdbFilterTable and swFdbStaticTable description also.

swMacBaseVlanAddrEntry.name: swMacBaseVlanAddrEntry
swMacBaseVlanAddrEntry.description: A list of information about a specific unicast or multicast MAC address for which the switch has some forwarding and/or filtering information.

swMacBaseVlanAddr.name: swMacBaseVlanAddr
swMacBaseVlanAddr.description: This object indictaes a unicast or multicast MAC address for which the bridge has forwarding and/or filtering information.

swMacBaseVlanAddrVlanDesc.name: swMacBaseVlanAddrVlanDesc
swMacBaseVlanAddrVlanDesc.description: A textual description of the Mac Base Vlan for memorization.

swMacBaseVlanAddrState.name: swMacBaseVlanAddrState
swMacBaseVlanAddrState.description: This object indicates the MacBase Vlan Address entry state. other(1) - this entry is currently in use but the conditions under which it will remain so are different from each of the following values. invalid(2) - writing this value to the object, and then the corresponding entry will be removed from the table. valid(3) - this entry is reside in the table.

swMacBaseVlanAddrStatus.name: swMacBaseVlanAddrStatus
swMacBaseVlanAddrStatus.description: This object indicates the MacBase Vlan Address entry state. other(1) - this entry is currently in use but the conditions under which it will remain so are different from each of the following values. apply(2) - this entry is currently in use and reside in the table. not-apply(3) - this entry is reside in the table but currently not in use due to conflict with filter table.

swPortBaseVlanTotalNum.name: swPortBaseVlanTotalNum
swPortBaseVlanTotalNum.description: The total number of Port-Base Vlan which is in enabled state within this switch hub.

swPortBaseVlanDefaultVlanTable.name: swPortBaseVlanDefaultVlanTable
swPortBaseVlanDefaultVlanTable.description: A table that contains default Port-Based VLAN list entries for the switch. The entry (Vid = 1,i.e. swPortBaseVlanDefaultPvid = 1) is defalut Port-Based VLAN , maintained by system.

swPortBaseVlanDefaultVlanEntry.name: swPortBaseVlanDefaultVlanEntry
swPortBaseVlanDefaultVlanEntry.description: A list of default Port-Based VLAN information in swPortBaseVlanDefaultVlanTable.

swPortBaseVlanDefaultPvid.name: swPortBaseVlanDefaultPvid
swPortBaseVlanDefaultPvid.description: This object indicates the default Port-Base Vlan ID. It occupies only 1 entry in VLAN table, with VID=1.

swPortBaseVlanDefaultDesc.name: swPortBaseVlanDefaultDesc
swPortBaseVlanDefaultDesc.description: A textual description of the Port-Base Vlan.

swPortBaseVlanDefaultPortList.name: swPortBaseVlanDefaultPortList
swPortBaseVlanDefaultPortList.description: This object indicates the port member set of the specified Vlan. Each Vlan has a octect string to indicate the port map. The most significant bit represents the lowest numbered port, and the least significant bit represents the highest numbered port.

swPortBaseVlanDefaultPortNumber.name: swPortBaseVlanDefaultPortNumber
swPortBaseVlanDefaultPortNumber.description: This object indicates the number of ports of the entry.

swPortBaseVlanConfigTable.name: swPortBaseVlanConfigTable
swPortBaseVlanConfigTable.description: A table that contains Port-Based VLAN list entries for the switch. The device can't support port overlapping in Port-Based VLAN.

swPortBaseVlanConfigEntry.name: swPortBaseVlanConfigEntry
swPortBaseVlanConfigEntry.description: A list of information about a specific Port-Based VLAN configuration in swPortBaseVlanConfigTable.

swPortBaseVlanConfigPvid.name: swPortBaseVlanConfigPvid
swPortBaseVlanConfigPvid.description: This object indicates the Port-Base Vlan ID. There are up to 11 entries for current product now. The object range varies from 2 to 12.

swPortBaseVlanConfigDesc.name: swPortBaseVlanConfigDesc
swPortBaseVlanConfigDesc.description: A textual description of the Port-Base Vlan. It cannot be a null string. And each description must be unique in the table.

swPortBaseVlanConfigPortList.name: swPortBaseVlanConfigPortList
swPortBaseVlanConfigPortList.description: This object indicates which ports are belong to the Vlan. Each Vlan has a octect string to indicate with port map. The most significant bit represents the lowest numbered port, and the least significant bit represents the highest numbered port.

swPortBaseVlanConfigPortNumber.name: swPortBaseVlanConfigPortNumber
swPortBaseVlanConfigPortNumber.description: This object indicates the number of ports of the entry.
